<section>
  <p>
    During October, 2018, we deployed Simple in 20 more clinics. A WhatsApp group kept us in touch with our early users and helped us maintain a short feedback loop to uncover and fix issues. It was inspiring to see how quickly nurses and doctors got accustomed to using Simple to record patients and how the app could help them recover hours of their precious time. Before Simple, clinicians spent a couple of minutes just to find each patient‚Äôs paper treatment card from a stack of hundreds, but now users only had to enter a patient‚Äôs name into the app to look up their record. Simple reduced the time to record a patient from 4‚Äì5 minutes to about 45 seconds.
  </p>
  <p>
    Over the last year, we made frequent, iterative improvements. We prototyped and tested constantly. And, we released new versions about every two weeks. In May, we introduced a scannable user ID called a ‚ÄúBP Passport‚Äù which has reduced data entry time to 24 seconds on average. Clinicians can now spend more time actually treating and counseling patients, rather than recording data.
  </p>
</section>
